# 🎓 ML Tutor Chatbot

ML Tutor Chatbot is a local AI-powered tutoring assistant for Machine Learning.  
It combines a local LLM, tutor-style prompting, and a simple RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) pipeline to help students learn concepts step-by-step.

---

## 🚀 Features

- 💬 Ask Machine Learning questions (theory + formulas)
- 📂 Upload notes (PDF, DOCX, TXT)
- 🔍 Retrieves relevant content from uploaded notes
- 🧠 Tutor-style responses:
  - Short answer
  - Intuition / analogy
  - Step-by-step explanation
  - Optional formula explanation
- 🎯 Adjustable difficulty (Beginner → Advanced)
- 🧪 Modes: Explain, Quiz, Hint
- ⚙️ Runs fully locally using Ollama

---

## 🏗️ Tech Stack

- Python  
- Streamlit (UI)  
- Ollama (Local LLM - Mistral)  
- Custom RAG Pipeline  
- LangChain utilities  

---

## ⚙️ Setup Instructions (Step-by-Step)

### 1. Clone the repository

git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/ML_tutor_chatbot.git  
cd ML_tutor_chatbot  

### 2. Create and activate virtual environment

python3 -m venv venv  
source venv/bin/activate   # Mac/Linux  

### 3. Install dependencies

pip install -r requirements.txt  

### 4. Install and setup Ollama

Download Ollama from https://ollama.com  

Pull the model using:  
ollama pull mistral  

Test the model:  
ollama run mistral  

Ask a simple ML question in terminal to verify it works.

### 5. Start Ollama server

ollama serve  

### 6. Run the Streamlit app

streamlit run app.py  

---

## 📂 Supported File Types

- PDF (typed text only)  
- DOCX  
- TXT  

⚠️ Handwritten or scanned PDFs may not work properly in this version.

---

## 🧠 How It Works

1. Upload notes  
2. Notes are extracted, chunked, and stored in the retriever  
3. When a question is asked, relevant chunks are retrieved  
4. Retrieved context is passed to the model  
5. The model responds in tutor-style format  

